Class WingsEndpoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.groundupworks.wings.WingsEndpoint

  • public abstract class WingsEndpoint

      • notifyLinkStateChanged

        protected <T extends WingsEndpoint.LinkEvent> void notifyLinkStateChanged(T event)
        Notifies subscribers that the link state has changed. Each endpoint implementation must call this method with its own WingsEndpoint.LinkEvent subclass when the link state has changed.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type for the WingsEndpoint.LinkEvent subclass.
        Parameters:
        event - the WingsEndpoint.LinkEvent implementation associated with the specific endpoint.

      • onActivityResultImpl

        public abstract void onActivityResultImpl(android.app.Activity activity,
                        Fragment fragment,
                        int requestCode,
                        int resultCode,
                        android.content.Intent data)
        A convenience method that must be called in the onActivityResult() of any Activity or android.support.v4.app.Fragment that uses #startLinkRequest(android.app.Activity, android.support.v4.app.Fragment).
        Parameters:
        activity - the Activity.
        fragment - the android.support.v4.app.Fragment. May be null.
        requestCode - the integer request code originally supplied to startActivityForResult(), allowing you to identify who this result came from.
        resultCode - the integer result code returned by the child activity through its setResult().
        data - an Intent, which can return result data to the caller (various data can be attached to Intent "extras").

      • processShareRequests

        public abstract java.util.Set<WingsEndpoint.ShareNotification> processShareRequests()
        Process share requests by sharing to the linked account. This should be called in a background thread.
        Returns:
        a set of WingsEndpoint.ShareNotifications representing the results of the processed ShareRequest. May be null or an empty set.

      • produceLinkEvent

        public abstract <T extends WingsEndpoint.LinkEvent> T produceLinkEvent()
        Produces a WingsEndpoint.LinkEvent subclass reflecting the current link state of the endpoint. This event is emitted to a subscriber immediately after subscription.

        The implementation of this method must be annotated with com.squareup.otto.Produce.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type for the WingsEndpoint.LinkEvent subclass.
        Returns:
        the WingsEndpoint.LinkEvent implementation associated with the specific endpoint.
